      "sub_topic": "COUNSELLING"
    },
    "clinical_category": "diagnosis",
    "text_content": "#### STOP TOBACCO AND AVOID HARMFUL USE OF ALCOHOL  \nEncourage all non-smokers not to start smoking\nStrongly advise all smokers to stop smoking and support them in their eff orts\nIndividuals who use other forms of tobacco should be advised to quit\nAlcohol abstinence should be reinforced.\nPeople should not be advised to start taking alcohol for health reasons\nAdvise patients not to use alcohol when additional risks are present, such as:\n– driving or operating machinery\n– pregnant or breast feeding\n– taking medications that interact with alcohol\n– medical conditions made worse by alcohol\n– diffi culties in controlling drinking",
    "extracted_tables": [],
    "page_reference": []
  },
  {
    "chunk_id": "who_pen_diesease_int_4b92b8db06",
    "domain_spoke": "chronic_care",
    "source_text": "who pen diesease interventions",
    "hierarchical_context": {
      "chapter": "DIABETES",
      "primary_topic": "EARLY DIAGNOSIS",
      "sub_topic": "COUNSELLING"
    },
    "clinical_category": "diagnosis",
    "text_content": "#### ADHERE TO TREATMENT  \nIf the patient is prescribed medication:\n– teach the patient how to take it at home\n– explain the diff erence between medicines for long- term control (e.g. blood\npressure) and medicines for quick relief (e.g. for wheezing)\n– tell the patient the reason for prescribing the medication\nShow the patient the appropriate dose\nExplain how many times a day to take the medication\nLabel and package the tablets\nCheck the patient’s understanding before the patient leaves the health centre\nExplain the importance of:\n– keeping an adequate supply of the medication\n– the need to take the medication regularly as advised even if there are no symptoms",
    "extracted_tables": [],
    "page_reference": []
  },
  {
    "chunk_id": "who_pen_diesease_int_fbb0e80f06",
    "domain_spoke": "chronic_care",
    "source_text": "who pen diesease interventions",
    "hierarchical_context": {
      "chapter": "DIABETES",
      "primary_topic": "EARLY DIAGNOSIS",
      "sub_topic": "COUNSELLING"
    },
    "clinical_category": "diagnosis",
    "text_content": "#### BE PHYSICALLY ACTIVE  \nProgressively increase physical activity to moderate levels (such as brisk walking)\nat least 30 minutes per day on 5 days of the week\nControl body weight and avoid overweight by reducing high-calorie food and\ntaking adequate physical activity",
    "extracted_tables": [],
    "page_reference": []
  },
  {
    "chunk_id": "who_pen_diesease_int_a53108086c",
    "domain_spoke": "chronic_care",
